{
  "stem": "15768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in some distance, but in the same car, was Christina who was supposed to make sure that everything was going well according to plan, that if something went wrong, she would be able to report it to Herbert at the meeting point where he was going to pick us up with his car.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she was wearing my mother's watch and her jewelry.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And at a very critical moment when the conductor was coming through the train, I spoke up in a very loud language and said, oh, look, Mommy.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This lady, she's got the same watch and the same necklace that you have.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They're identical.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I think my mother just barely managed [LAUGHS] to shush me up in time and-- and end the subject.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We then met Herbert Kramer at a small station where we got off the train and got into his car.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not really.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- we had the-- my mother had a passport with a large J on the-- on the passport itself.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And other than that, we were really illegal in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The way that she had procured these-- these permits was that the-- Christina went-- there was a little bit of a look-a-like, not terribly so but close enough-- that Christina used to take these things to the official bureaus, and they would stamp them and OK them and not put a J for Jewish on these papers and therefore OK them.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then afterwards, somehow the J got onto the papers as we left.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But she did all this type of thing which enabled-- which enabled us really to do it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If the J had been in there, we may never have, you know, been able to get out of the country.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
